{
  "message": "fix(abi): correct statfs f_flags offset and refresh conformance snapshots\n\n- Fix statfs_to_statvfs f_flags byte offset from 104 to 80 to match the\n  actual x86_64 kernel struct statfs layout (type=0, bsize=8, blocks=16,\n  bfree=24, bavail=32, files=40, ffree=48, fsid=56, namelen=64,\n  frsize=72, flags=80). The previous offset of 104 read past the flags\n  field into the spare array, returning garbage values for mount flags.\n\n- Regenerate conformance coverage snapshot and support matrix maintenance\n  report to reflect the expanded ABI surface from the previous commit.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
  "files": [
    {
      "sha": "754368b1c0df70c1cd2bce3045e89d85751823aa",
      "filename": "crates/frankenlibc-abi/src/unistd_abi.rs",
      "status": "modified",
      "additions": 3,
      "deletions": 2,
      "changes": 5,
      "blob_url": "https://github.com/Dicklesworthstone/frankenlibc/blob/95a8d3af4531eba08a7752de8b22d48bc33f011f/crates%2Ffrankenlibc-abi%2Fsrc%2Funistd_abi.rs",
      "raw_url": "https://github.com/Dicklesworthstone/frankenlibc/raw/95a8d3af4531eba08a7752de8b22d48bc33f011f/crates%2Ffrankenlibc-abi%2Fsrc%2Funistd_abi.rs",
      "contents_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Dicklesworthstone/frankenlibc/contents/crates%2Ffrankenlibc-abi%2Fsrc%2Funistd_abi.rs?ref=95a8d3af4531eba08a7752de8b22d48bc33f011f",
      "patch": "@@ -10135,9 +10135,10 @@ unsafe fn statfs_to_statvfs(sfs: *const libc::statfs, vfs: *mut libc::statvfs) {\n     let fsid_ptr = &s.f_fsid as *const libc::fsid_t as *const i32;\n     v.f_fsid = unsafe { *fsid_ptr } as u64;\n     // f_flags not exposed in libc crate's statfs; read via byte offset\n-    // kernel layout: ..., namelen(off=88), frsize(off=96), flags(off=104) \u2014 all c_long\n+    // x86_64 kernel layout: type(0), bsize(8), blocks(16), bfree(24), bavail(32),\n+    // files(40), ffree(48), fsid(56), namelen(64), frsize(72), flags(80), spare(88)\n     let statfs_ptr = sfs as *const u8;\n-    let flags_val = unsafe { *(statfs_ptr.add(104) as *const i64) };\n+    let flags_val = unsafe { *(statfs_ptr.add(80) as *const i64) };\n     v.f_flag = flags_val as u64;\n     v.f_namemax = s.f_namelen as u64;\n }"
    },
